      {
        "id": "37eb572de799ba880385be23eff17e42187ac0f6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-13 12:39:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI feel this kind of packages are problematic as they are not needed and not documented anywhere that are here just for testing...",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "e298dfeb1990a3a1b605fc88cb9049eac7ca4bb1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4886,
          "name": "Petr Ospalý",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "p.ospaly@email.cz",
          "username": "p.ospaly"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-13 13:33:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Samuli screen has 795.01 KB, jq has 350.82 KB, dependency oniguruma has 555.09 KB - how 1.5MB of extra binaries (installed, rpms are even less) compare with ten GBs of ONAP?\n\nOn the other side - screen is the first thing I need as sysadmin. Because if anything ONAP related takes hours to finish then I don't want to hope that my ssh session will not die - I can just let it running and go home.\n\nJq is needed because it is the only sensible thing how to manipulate json - using sed is masochism. Why to manipulate json? Maybe because things like this: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/reconfigure-kubelet/#generate-the-configuration-file",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "85501b5ecbe88e9f887394cec4c59dc01af56373",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-13 18:16:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> @Samuli screen has 795.01 KB, jq has 350.82 KB, dependency oniguruma has 555.09 KB - how 1.5MB of extra binaries (installed, rpms are even less) compare with ten GBs of ONAP?\n> \n> On the other side - screen is the first thing I need as sysadmin. Because if anything ONAP related takes hours to finish then I don't want to hope that my ssh session will not die - I can just let it running and go home.\n> \n> Jq is needed because it is the only sensible thing how to manipulate json - using sed is masochism. Why to manipulate json? Maybe because things like this: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/reconfigure-kubelet/#generate-the-configuration-file\n\nYes, I did not commented the size or usefulness of tools.\nJust the fact that users should know what binaries are for what.\nEither document or create own file to make it clear the purpose.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
